  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2004-07-12",
    "date": "2004-07-26T17:10:59Z",
    "text": "Designates September 2004 as Service for Seniors Month.\n\nRecognizes the need for companionship and assistance with daily tasks among seniors with long-term health conditions throughout the year. Encourages: (1) the people of the United States to volunteer regularly with homebound frail elderly or at a nursing home or long-term care facility; (2) volunteer organizations that offer companionship and assistance to seniors to incorporate Service for Seniors Month in their recruitment efforts; and (3) individuals to volunteer in these service organizations."
